A [[Sarvastivada]] school, Kusha-shū focused on [[:en:Abhidharma|Abhidharma]] analysis based on the "Commentary on the {{nihongo|''[[:en:Abhidharma-kosa|Abhidharmakośabhaṣya]]''|倶舎論}}" by the fourth-century [[:en:Gandhara|Gandhara]]n philosopher [[Vasubandhu]]. The school takes its name from that authoritative text.{{sfn|Buswell|Lopez|2013|p=574}}

Names commonly associated with the Kusha-shū are [[:en:Dōshō|Dōshō]] (道昭 638–700), Joe (644–714), Chitsū (智通 ?–?), Chitatsu (智達 ?–?), and [[:en:Genbō|Genbō]] (玄昉 ?–746).

